  "text": "In an attempt to describe hydrocarbon mixture properties, early models relied on the techniques of lumping [CITATION_1] , where a relatively small number of lumps were used to describe the mixture. In these coarsely lumped kinetic models, thousands of individual constituents in a complex feedstock were grouped into broad but measurable categories of compound classes or boiling range, with simplified reaction networks between the lumps.",
